cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL 

The paper discusses a model for learning representations of local image contents and pixel displacements caused by relative motions, which is relevant to computer vision (cs.CV). The use of machine learning to learn these representations suggests that it could also fall under neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper proposes a representational model of V1, which could be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) as it pertains to understanding how the brain processes visual information.
